00:56:42,921 --> 00:56:43,965
Three.

816
00:56:49,275 --> 00:56:52,800
Tell me something.
Are you ever wrong?

817
00:56:55,281 --> 00:56:57,239
No.

818
00:56:57,283 --> 00:56:59,807
I may not always be right,
but I'm never wrong.

819
00:57:03,594 --> 00:57:05,987
Definitely, it's not
French at all.

820
00:57:06,031 --> 00:57:07,598
Not hungry, huh?

821
00:57:11,340 --> 00:57:12,994
Oh, yeah. I've got to show
you something wonderful.

822
00:57:13,038 --> 00:57:14,909
Yeah? Yeah.

823
00:57:14,953 --> 00:57:16,258
You see all this water?

824
00:57:16,302 --> 00:57:17,434
It's a river called the Seine.

825
00:57:17,477 --> 00:57:18,609
Yeah.

826
00:57:18,652 --> 00:57:20,611
And it goes directly
into the sea.

827
00:57:20,654 --> 00:57:23,744
I'm sorry. It throws
itself into the sea.

828
00:57:23,788 --> 00:57:25,311
You know that?

829
00:57:30,795 --> 00:57:32,840
[SPEAKS FRENCH]

830
00:57:34,407 --> 00:57:36,365
XAVIER: Shit.

831
00:57:36,409 --> 00:57:38,455
What's the matter?

832
00:57:38,498 --> 00:57:40,326
I'll be right back.

833
00:57:45,723 --> 00:57:47,464
[CONVERSING IN FRENCH]

834
00:58:08,920 --> 00:58:09,703
[SIGHS]

835
00:58:31,029 --> 00:58:32,726
Are you all right?

836
00:58:34,554 --> 00:58:35,512
I'm fine.

837
00:59:01,712 --> 00:59:03,888
Hurray! You made it.

838
00:59:03,931 --> 00:59:05,716
Hi, Philip. Hi.

839
00:59:06,412 --> 00:59:08,370
Hello. Hello. Oh!

840
00:59:08,414 --> 00:59:09,850
This is Mo. And I'm Philip.

841
00:59:09,894 --> 00:59:11,722
Philip. Hi.

842
00:59:11,765 --> 00:59:13,854
Well, I think my wife's
around here somewhere.

843
00:59:13,898 --> 00:59:16,030
Never mind. I'll show you
to your room. Come on in.

844
00:59:16,074 --> 00:59:18,598
[SPEAKS FRENCH]

845
00:59:20,252 --> 00:59:21,122
So how was the drive?

846
00:59:21,166 --> 00:59:23,081
Oh, wonderful.

847
00:59:23,124 --> 00:59:24,691
Come on in.

848
00:59:24,735 --> 00:59:27,259
I have got something
for you. Go ahead.

849
00:59:27,302 --> 00:59:29,696
Well, you know your way.

850
00:59:29,740 --> 00:59:30,741
Come on in.

851
00:59:35,354 --> 00:59:37,095
And here we are.

852
00:59:38,749 --> 00:59:41,055
What a beautiful old house.

853
00:59:41,099 --> 00:59:43,144
Well, I hope you'll be
comfortable here.

854
00:59:43,188 --> 00:59:46,713
Yeah, the nights have been
rather chilly recently.

855
00:59:46,757 --> 00:59:49,803
I think you may well
need one of these.

856
00:59:49,847 --> 00:59:51,065
Ah, let me see
what else is there.

857
00:59:51,109 --> 00:59:52,980
Oh, yes. Bathroom's
through that door there.

858
00:59:53,024 --> 00:59:55,417
It's all rather rustic,
I'm afraid.

859
00:59:55,461 --> 00:59:57,202
Now, this is France.

860
00:59:59,770 --> 01:00:02,120
[SOFTLY] You've done
well for a banker.

861
01:00:02,163 --> 01:00:04,426
Oh. Oh!

862
01:00:04,470 --> 01:00:07,125
Oh, wonderful. Thank you.

863
01:00:07,821 --> 01:00:12,086
Well, I'll leave you
to sort yourselves out.

864
01:00:12,130 --> 01:00:14,088
Oh, oh, by the way, we'll begoing into the village later on,

865
01:00:14,132 --> 01:00:16,656
if anybody wants to come.

866
01:00:16,700 --> 01:00:17,701
There's a big dance
there, on Sunday,

867
01:00:17,744 --> 01:00:20,094
and we're helping
them set it up.

868
01:00:20,138 --> 01:00:22,357
Well, I'll see you later.

869
01:00:25,317 --> 01:00:26,623
[BOY SHOUTING]

870
01:00:37,198 --> 01:00:37,938
Is that Philip's wife?

871
01:00:37,982 --> 01:00:39,592
Yes.

872
01:00:40,985 --> 01:00:43,465
Hi, Sylvia. Hi.

873
01:00:43,509 --> 01:00:44,945
Are they friends with Isabelle?

874
01:00:44,989 --> 01:00:47,600
No, Sylvia and Isabelle
are worlds apart.

875
01:00:49,515 --> 01:00:51,038
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

876
01:00:55,216 --> 01:00:56,522
Mum and Daddy.

877
01:01:03,224 --> 01:01:04,835
[CHATTERING IN FRENCH]

878
01:01:49,575 --> 01:01:50,881
[CONVERSING IN FRENCH]

879
01:01:52,883 --> 01:01:55,059
I like her.

880
01:01:55,102 --> 01:01:56,016
So does Xavier.

881
01:01:56,060 --> 01:01:58,279
[LAUGHS] I can see that.

882
01:01:58,323 --> 01:01:59,716
[BAND RESUMES PLAYING]

883
01:02:04,416 --> 01:02:06,766
[CONVERSING IN FRENCH]

884
01:02:06,810 --> 01:02:08,246
Oh, yes.

885
01:02:08,812 --> 01:02:10,465
See you.

886
01:02:12,076 --> 01:02:14,165
[WOMAN SINGING FRENCH SONG]

887
01:02:33,314 --> 01:02:34,751
[SLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

888
01:03:04,737 --> 01:03:06,826
Do you love Isabelle?

889
01:03:06,870 --> 01:03:09,481
Ah! She's an exceptional woman.

890
01:03:09,524 --> 01:03:12,179
I know. I know.
But do you love her?

891
01:03:13,441 --> 01:03:16,096
We're very good together,
we're just like that?

892
01:03:16,140 --> 01:03:18,533
You're not answering
my question.

893
01:03:20,187 --> 01:03:21,406
Look.

894
01:03:22,842 --> 01:03:24,235
Drop it.

895
01:03:25,627 --> 01:03:28,152
You don't understand.
It's none of your business.

896
01:03:37,770 --> 01:03:39,250
Come on now.

897
01:03:40,860 --> 01:03:42,427
Let's dance.

898
01:03:57,268 --> 01:03:59,226
Tell me.

899
01:03:59,270 --> 01:04:01,663
Were you always in love
with your husband?

900
01:04:01,707 --> 01:04:03,840
Yes. Very much so.

901
01:04:03,883 --> 01:04:05,232
Then why did you divorce him?

902
01:04:06,886 --> 01:04:08,932
I didn't divorce him.
He divorced me.

903
01:04:12,805 --> 01:04:14,589
He didn't love me anymore.

904
01:04:29,735 --> 01:04:31,737
That's not a valid reason.

905
01:04:44,228 --> 01:04:46,708
All right.

906
01:04:46,752 --> 01:04:48,928
Perhaps I don't love my wife.

907
01:04:49,929 --> 01:04:53,237
But I need her,
and she needs me.

908
01:04:53,280 --> 01:04:55,108
And it was in both our interests

909
01:04:55,152 --> 01:04:58,546
to get married
and to stay married.

910
01:04:58,590 --> 01:05:01,636
And then you have others for
love affairs like this...

911
01:05:02,159 --> 01:05:03,464
What's her name?

912
01:05:03,508 --> 01:05:04,944
Nathalie.

913
01:05:06,337 --> 01:05:08,730
How long have you
been seeing her?

914
01:05:08,774 --> 01:05:11,733
On and off for three years.

915
01:05:11,777 --> 01:05:13,953
And there were
others before her?

916
01:05:13,997 --> 01:05:14,736
A few.

917
01:05:14,780 --> 01:05:17,087
That's horrible.

918
01:05:17,130 --> 01:05:19,176
You're being naive, Mo.

919
01:05:20,960 --> 01:05:23,832
And Isabelle doesn't care?
Or doesn't she know?

920
01:05:23,876 --> 01:05:25,791
I make sure she doesn't.

921
01:05:29,621 --> 01:05:32,406
You must put on some
really good shows.

922
01:05:32,450 --> 01:05:33,930
I try to be diplomatic.

923
01:05:34,974 --> 01:05:37,107
Diplomatic?

924
01:05:37,150 --> 01:05:39,326
That's not diplomacy.
That's duplicity.

925
01:05:41,154 --> 01:05:42,634
It's pathetic.

926
01:05:44,288 --> 01:05:45,811
All of you.

927
01:05:45,854 --> 01:05:47,944
You, your wife, your mistresses.

928
01:05:47,987 --> 01:05:49,771
Wait a second!

929
01:05:49,815 --> 01:05:52,078
You are one of my mistresses.
You know it.

930
01:05:52,122 --> 01:05:55,342
And you knew I was
married when you met me.

931
01:05:55,908 --> 01:05:58,302
You reason like a child!
Grow up!

932
01:06:18,409 --> 01:06:19,366
Mo.

933
01:06:20,019 --> 01:06:22,152
Go away.

934
01:06:22,195 --> 01:06:23,675
What are you doing?

935
01:06:25,024 --> 01:06:27,374
I'm digging holes.

936
01:06:27,418 --> 01:06:29,507
[VOICE BREAKING]
For the lavender.

937
01:06:39,691 --> 01:06:40,997
You can't see a thing.

938
01:06:42,781 --> 01:06:46,350
I don't need to see.
I do it by touch.

939
01:06:59,406 --> 01:07:00,886
[SIGHING]

940
01:07:03,193 --> 01:07:06,196
You don't take me
seriously, do you?

941
01:07:06,239 --> 01:07:07,632
Of course I do.

942
01:07:12,115 --> 01:07:13,551
No, you don't.

943
01:07:16,119 --> 01:07:18,469
You take your wife seriously.

944
01:07:23,256 --> 01:07:25,563
And you take your
mistresses seriously.

945
01:07:30,089 --> 01:07:31,438
But I'm just a

946
01:07:33,223 --> 01:07:34,659
odd girl

947
01:07:36,226 --> 01:07:38,141
to fill up an odd month

948
01:07:39,794 --> 01:07:42,580
that you really didn't
know what to do with.

949
01:07:44,147 --> 01:07:45,931
But, Mo,

950
01:07:46,975 --> 01:07:50,240
that was our agreement,
wasn't it?

951
01:07:53,591 --> 01:07:55,854
Everything's been so beautiful.

952
01:07:57,029 --> 01:07:58,944
Let's not ruin it.

953
01:07:59,640 --> 01:08:01,947
Don't spoil the memories.

954
01:08:02,948 --> 01:08:03,862
[SIGHS]

955
01:08:06,952 --> 01:08:08,084
Memories?

956
01:08:24,709 --> 01:08:26,928
I have to get up in four hours.

957
01:08:26,972 --> 01:08:28,930
If you want to stay
here with Sylvia,

958
01:08:28,974 --> 01:08:30,976
while Philip and I are in Paris?

959
01:08:40,986 --> 01:08:42,727
You're strange sometimes.

960
01:08:48,211 --> 01:08:49,342
[SIGHS]

961
01:08:57,176 --> 01:08:58,134
[SIGHS]

962
01:09:36,520 --> 01:09:39,000
SOPHIE: And then, he had
to go and catch him.

963
01:09:39,044 --> 01:09:43,309
And then, afterwards, he turns
him over and he became black.

964
01:09:43,353 --> 01:09:44,571
Then he became...

965
01:09:44,615 --> 01:09:46,399
Oh, thank you.

966
01:09:47,792 --> 01:09:49,185
She's so cute.

967
01:09:49,228 --> 01:09:51,361
SYLVIA: Yeah, I think so, too.

968
01:09:51,404 --> 01:09:53,841
Look. Don't be so upset.

969
01:09:53,885 --> 01:09:55,756
You fell in love
with a married man.

970
01:09:56,757 --> 01:10:00,935
I know. I did it myself.
It always hurts.

971
01:10:01,893 --> 01:10:02,807
You understand?

972
01:10:04,374 --> 01:10:05,636
Yes.

973
01:10:07,246 --> 01:10:08,813
I understand.

974
01:10:10,249 --> 01:10:13,209
And it wasn't so bad, was it?

975
01:10:15,776 --> 01:10:17,648
No, I guess not.

976
01:10:26,396 --> 01:10:28,267
SOPHIE: Oh, the ball
fell in the water.

977
01:10:28,311 --> 01:10:29,268
[SOPHIE SCREAMS]
[WATER SPLASHES]

978
01:10:29,312 --> 01:10:31,357
Sophie! [DOG BARKING]

979
01:10:31,401 --> 01:10:32,358
Oh, my God.

980
01:10:32,402 --> 01:10:33,403
Sophie!

981
01:10:37,407 --> 01:10:38,886
Sophie! Sophie!

982
01:10:38,930 --> 01:10:40,975
Look under the boat!

983
01:10:41,019 --> 01:10:43,413
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

984
01:10:43,456 --> 01:10:45,110
Colonel Viola has assured me

985
01:10:45,153 --> 01:10:47,373
that the national
deficit will be

986
01:10:47,417 --> 01:10:49,245
substantially less
than what we expected.

987
01:10:53,466 --> 01:10:55,076
How's she doing?

988
01:10:55,120 --> 01:10:56,774
[SOBBING] I don't know.

989
01:10:59,429 --> 01:11:01,648
She's going to be
all right. Okay?

990
01:11:04,129 --> 01:11:05,913
As will you see,
these guidelines

991
01:11:05,957 --> 01:11:08,176
conform to IMF standards.

992
01:11:08,655 --> 01:11:13,094
We will cut imports
to $17 billion

993
01:11:13,138 --> 01:11:15,749
from $20.5 billion.

994
01:11:15,793 --> 01:11:17,142
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

995
01:11:21,451 --> 01:11:22,756
SYLVIA: Mo, please hurry.

996
01:11:22,800 --> 01:11:24,280
Oh, shit. Where do we go?

997
01:11:25,716 --> 01:11:27,152
Watch out!

998
01:11:31,809 --> 01:11:33,289
[HONKING]

999
01:11:34,420 --> 01:11:37,815
These changes will be
particularly effective

1000
01:11:37,858 --> 01:11:40,426
in the agricultural
infrastructure.

1001
01:11:40,470 --> 01:11:42,123
When are we gonna stop
behaving like gamblers

1002
01:11:42,167 --> 01:11:43,864
and start behaving like bankers?

1003
01:11:43,908 --> 01:11:46,650
Oh, Carry. Please,
let's hear him out.

1004
01:11:46,693 --> 01:11:48,782
We all know that
the consequences are...

1005
01:11:48,826 --> 01:11:50,915
Philip, it's Sylvia.
We have to go.

1006
01:11:53,047 --> 01:11:54,527
Come on!

1007
01:11:54,571 --> 01:11:57,008
[PEOPLE MURMURING]

1008
01:11:57,922 --> 01:11:59,315
[BABY CRYING]

1009
01:12:09,368 --> 01:12:11,892
Hello, darling. Yes, you are.

1010
01:12:11,936 --> 01:12:13,372
[THANKING IN FRENCH]

1011
01:12:13,938 --> 01:12:15,156
There they are. 
Sylvia!

1012
01:12:15,200 --> 01:12:16,506
I know it. 
