[SPEAKS FRENCH]

1078
01:18:49,986 --> 01:18:51,944
Oh, no, it's not working.

1079
01:18:51,988 --> 01:18:53,772
Oh, I'll go up the stairs.
Can I help you?

1080
01:18:53,816 --> 01:18:55,469
Oh, thank you. Thank you.

1081
01:18:56,514 --> 01:18:57,776
It's heavy.

1082
01:18:59,909 --> 01:19:01,562
What's in there?

1083
01:19:01,606 --> 01:19:03,782
Oh, it's a little rabbit. It's
for my niece in Missouri.

1084
01:19:03,826 --> 01:19:05,958
[CHUCKLES] He's very sweet.

1085
01:19:06,002 --> 01:19:07,743
Are you going to the top floor?

1086
01:19:07,786 --> 01:19:09,919
Yes. Are you
a friend of Chantal?

1087
01:19:09,962 --> 01:19:11,224
Oh, no.

1088
01:19:11,268 --> 01:19:12,617
MO: Oh.

1089
01:19:13,792 --> 01:19:15,925
[BIDDING FAREWELL IN FRENCH]

1090
01:19:21,974 --> 01:19:24,324
Xavier. Uh...

1091
01:19:24,368 --> 01:19:26,413
This is for Mo. From Sophie.

1092
01:19:26,457 --> 01:19:28,372
That's very sweet. Thank you.

1093
01:19:33,377 --> 01:19:35,509
Look, I...

1094
01:19:35,553 --> 01:19:38,643
I hope you come down to the
country and see us again soon.

1095
01:19:38,686 --> 01:19:40,601
And I know that
Sophie and Sylvia

1096
01:19:40,645 --> 01:19:42,429
would both love to see Mo again

1097
01:19:42,473 --> 01:19:43,517
before she leaves.

1098
01:19:44,649 --> 01:19:47,608
And, thank you.

1099
